# HTML Components

## Why

Using React or Angular can be a lot for projects that don't require complexity. That's why I came up with a quick solution.

## How to use

- `build.js` must be at the root of the project.
- `dev/` must also be at the root of the project, it contains your website.
- Components are `.html` files located in `dev/components/`.
- To add a component to your page, add the tag `<component src="nameOfYourComponent"></component>`, it will import the file located in `dev/components/nameOfYourComponent.html`.
- During dev, make sur to include `componentSupport.js`, it will take care of the rendering of your components
- Once you are done developping, execute `node build.js`. It will create a folder called `build/UTC_DATETIME_OF_BUILD/` containing your website with the components rendered statically.

### Quick example

#### During dev

It should look like this during dev, with `<script src="/dev/componentSupport.js" defer></script>` in the `head` or `body`.

```html
<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
    <head>
        <meta charset="UTF-8" />
        <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
        <title>HTML Components</title>
        <script src="/dev/componentSupport.js" defer></script>
        <!-- ESSENTIAL DURING DEV -->
    </head>
    <body>
        <component src="nameOfYourComponent"></component>
        <!-- ADDING A COMPONENT TO THE PAGE -->
    </body>
</html>
```

#### After build

It should look like this after building, `componentSupport.js` is now gone and your component has been directly baked in your page.

```html
<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
    <head>
        <meta charset="UTF-8" />
        <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
        <title>HTML Components</title>
    </head>
    <body>
        <!-- START OF COMPONENT -->
        <div>
            <h1>This is a component</h1>
            <h2>Everything has to be wrapped in a single element! <em>Not sure what to use?</em> Use a div!</h2>
        </div>
        <!-- END OF COMPONENT -->
    </body>
</html>
```

## Notice

 - This does not support recursivity, components **CANNOT** contain another component.
 - Components must be a single elements, if you have multiple elements, wrap them in a `div` or any other element of your choice.